                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="18011081" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 05:04:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This changed camel-jetty, so we need to look into that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011083" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 05:18:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The old code was actually correct - the relative path is appended like a proxy scenario. If you want to call an absolute url, you need to remove the headers, or use ignore control headers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011087" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 05:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay you need to do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot/commit/6f90b8b6b73687fe90926a861fa5bfe5a5890272&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot/commit/6f90b8b6b73687fe90926a861fa5bfe5a5890272&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also fixed something in camel-http. I have backported to 4.10.x branches.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011097" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 06:40:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In 4.10.x you need to remove that CamelHttpPath header due to skipControlHeaders is not an option yet&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot/commit/3852fdbc478c3bbf48dcfabe4dff355c0c4a67bf&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot/commit/3852fdbc478c3bbf48dcfabe4dff355c0c4a67bf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011098" author="JIRAUSER284142" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 06:45:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m expecting that in 4.10.x it was not necessary to remove the header in the route since there is this commit &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/18759&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/camel/pull/18759&lt;/a&gt;, am I wrong?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011101" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 06:51:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No we had to revert back to as before, and then for 4.10.x you need to remove the header if you want it like that - the old logic is correct, the bridge is appending relative paths, and since you do a rest on GET /mock then the relative path is /mock. And if you want to call an absolute path then remove the CamelHTTP headers that has always been the case. The new skipControlHeaders option make this easier so you can just set it = true instead of removing headers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011106" author="JIRAUSER284142" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 07:18:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I noticed a different behaviour when &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/camel-spring-boot/blob/main/components-starter/camel-platform-http-starter/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/platform/http/springboot/SpringBootPlatformHttpBinding.java#L299&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this override&lt;/a&gt; has been implemented, the parent  implementation returns a different value, so I needed to remove the header&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18011205" author="JIRAUSER284142" created="Thu, 31 Jul 2025 14:24:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was wondering if we should also ignore HTTP_PATH, same as HTTP_URI, in case of a bridged endpoint. I think it makes sense, in case we want to use the same path as the parent REST, we can append the HTTP_PATH again. Before the previous override, the HTTP_PATH was always empty if we used the Spring Boot runtime.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    </comments>
